HEADWORD: Surangular
<hw>Sur*an"gu*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>sur-</ets> + <ets>angular</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Above the angular bone; supra-angular; -- applied to a bone of the
lower jaw in many reptiles and birds.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>The surangular bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

